title: Quobyte: Devices
agents: quobyte
catalog: os/storage
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the devices of a Quobyte storage cluster, queried
 via the Quobyte WebAPI special agent.

 For each device it reports the mount path, serial number, optional label,
 the device mode and the health status. The device mode is mapped to a
 monitoring state via the configured warning and critical state lists. A
 health status other than HEALTHY or DECOMMISSIONED results in CRIT.

 The disk usage of the device is checked using the standard filesystem
 logic. Usage levels (in percent) can be configured via the rule
 "Quobyte devices". Default levels are 90%/95%.

item:
 The device ID.

discovery:
 One service is created for each device.
